title: Your gig guide to a great night out in Ipswich
text:
Your gig guide to a great night out in Ipswich 1st Oct 2015 12:00 PM See Devilâ€™s Kiosk perform at the Royal Mail Hotel. Contributed 
FIVE-DAY gig guide to the best entertainment in Ipswich. 

Thursday 
Waghorn Diner/ Jam Night Thursdays, Live music from 7pm, weekly jam night open to all musicians from amateurs to professionals. Begins at 7pm at Hotel Metropole. 
Springlake Hotel, Springfield Lakes Bvd / Thirsty Thursdays Free pool and sausage sizzle. Bikini waitresses from 2pm-5pm. Registration at 6pm to play poker. 
Brothers Leagues Club / Morning Melodies / Marco is performing from 11am in the O Bar. 
Ipswich RSL Club, Lowry St, Nth Ipswich / Live music, Bob Mildren will perform live from 11am - 2pm. 
Friday 
Royal Mail Hotel, Goodna / Live music, Izania performs from 7pm-10pm. Free entry, food and drinks available to purchase. 
Ipswich RSL Club, Lowry St, Nth Ipswich / Live music, 7.45pm-11.45pm. Smooth and Groove will play music to fill the dance floor. Entry as per RSL policy. 
Brothers Leagues Club / Able Magwitch will perform from 7.30pm in the O Bar followed by The London Cartel in the Sports Bar from 9.30pm. 
Springlake Hotel / Retro night / DJs spinning from 9.30pm -1.30am. 
Saturday 
Royal Mail Hotel, Goodna / Live music / Moondog performs live from 12.30pm-3.30pm followed by Devil's Kiosk from 4pm-7pm. 
Brothers Leagues Club / Live music to be performed by Family Affair in the O Bar at 7.30pm, with Vertigo playing at 9.30pm in the Sports Bar. 
Springlake Hotel / Some of Brisbane's best cover bands perform from 9.30pm - 1.30am. 
Commercial Hotel, Redbank / Southern Cross Poker tournament. Free to enter with cash prizes to be won. Registration is at 6pm with the game starting at 7pm. 
Sunday 
Royal Mail Hotel, Goodna / Live music / Pop Standen perform from 2pm. 
Brothers Leagues Club / Live music / Wally and the Gators are set to perform from 2pm - 6pm in the O Bar. 
Spicers Hidden Vale / Sunday Jazz. Enjoy a jazz duo in the idyllic surrounds of the Spicers Hidden Vale from noon-4pm. Bookings are essential for the served lunch. Phone 1300 179 340. 

Later in the Week 
Brothers Leagues Club / Australian Pro Poker / Monday and Wednesdays from 6pm. 
Ipswich RSL Club, Lowry St, Nth Ipswich / Every Wednesday / Live music, Country and Western Night, Michael King will perform live from 6.30pm - 9.30pm. gig guide
